parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The ABS warning light illuminates
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle experiences extended stopping distances
the vehicle locks up or jerks when applying the brakes
the brake fluid level is empty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt anchorage can cause the seatbelt to become detached, leading to increased risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The seatbelt clip or hook becomes detached from the floor anchor
the seatbelt does not stay attached to the floor
the seatbelt anchorage releases frequently when in use
the spring clip is broken or fails to hold.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, slow down, or come to a sudden stop, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power
the transmission makes grinding or whining noises
the vehicle slows down or comes to a sudden stop
the transmission fails to engage into gear
the speedometer fails to work.
